---
/**
 * ai-infrastructure/0001 · Figure 5 — Module 3,
 * "Recall ↔ latency ↔ memory: pick your point" (the ANN trade triangle).
 * Verbatim from the source HTML. No arrowhead markers used.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 220"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The recall-latency-memory triangle: pushing one corner pulls the others; the search knob slides along the recall-latency axis."
    >
        <text x="300" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Recall &harr; latency &harr; memory: pick your point</text
        >
        <!-- triangle -->
        <polygon points="300,46 110,176 490,176" fill="none" stroke="#1f3a5a" stroke-width="1.6"
        ></polygon>
        <text x="300" y="40" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >RECALL</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >found the true neighbors?</text
        >
        <text x="96" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >LATENCY</text
        >
        <text x="96" y="204" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >wider search = slower</text
        >
        <text x="504" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#8a5a0f"
            >MEMORY</text
        >
        <text x="504" y="204" text-anchor="middle" font-size="7.5" fill="#6b675f"
            >graph degree = RAM</text
        >
        <!-- knob slider -->
        <line x1="200" y1="120" x2="400" y2="120" stroke="#b5179e" stroke-width="2"></line>
        <circle cx="330" cy="120" r="6" fill="#b5179e"></circle>
        <text x="300" y="108" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >ef / nprobe</text
        >
        <text x="300" y="142" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" font-style="italic" fill="#6b675f"
            >slide right: more recall, more latency</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Every ANN deployment is a chosen point on this triangle. The search-breadth knob (<code
            >ef</code
        >
        for HNSW, <code>nprobe</code> for IVF) slides you along recall&harr;latency; build-time degree
        (<code>M</code>) and quantization trade memory. There is no setting that maximizes all
        three.<sup><a href="#s3" id="r3c">3</a></sup>
    </figcaption>
</figure>
